<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">variant</ENAMEX> forms): <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">cities</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">towns</ENAMEX>, lakes and rivers,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">mountains</ENAMEX> and valleys, even <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">facilities</ENAMEX> such as
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">schools</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">parks</ENAMEX>, and cemeteries.  The names themselves,
along with precise locational data and identification
by type, have been painstakingly keyboarded
into machine-readable form from the most
detailed <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">USGS</ENAMEX> topographic maps, the so-called <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">7.5-minute</TIMEX>
series.  Drawn to a scale of <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">1</NUMEX>:<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">24,000</NUMEX>, each
<TIMEX TYPE="TIME">7.5-minute</TIMEX> map sheet or quadrangle covers an area
