<ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">states</ENAMEX>.  Since it was intended to establish a standard,
the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">GNIS</ENAMEX> is very regular in format and is compiled
and maintained according to carefully prepared procedures.
This daunting task is overseen by the
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">USGS</ENAMEX>, specifically the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Branch of Domestic Names</ENAMEX>,
now under the direction of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Roger Payne</ENAMEX>.  Less comprehensive
government files are also maintained by
the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bureau of the Census</ENAMEX> (listing <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">about 60,000</NUMEX> populated
